				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1067304/navarro-saves-christmas#post-4060247</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 16 Nov 2018 15:41:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>LilyTide</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1825637</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I love it.</p> <p>It was sort of odd that there wasn't more dialogue. In my mental image, all of this is happening in near total silence, which of course is somewhat silly to imagine.</p> <p>But there is genuine warmth here. and as someone who has missed the last 5 Christmases and the last 4 thanksgivings, this strikes very close to home. It's always better when a coworker takes it upon themselves to kickstart the holiday spirit in whatever way they can.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
